abstract: An article last Tuesday about a new three-dimensional chat service from Google misidentified the university whose students helped test the service. It is Arizona State University, not the University of Arizona.

abstract: A big advertising technology firm says ads on Google for the same keywords cost more than on Yahoo. It worries that the pending deal in which Google will sell ads for Yahoo will raise prices for advertisers.
snippet: A big advertising technology firm says ads on Google for the same keywords cost more than on Yahoo. It worries that the pending deal in which Google will sell ads for Yahoo will raise prices for advertisers.
lead_paragraph: It’s not a surprise that search advertisers are wary of Yahoo’s deal to have some of its search ads sold by Google. After all, that extra money that Yahoo is hoping to get from the arrangement is coming from somewhere: the pocketbooks of advertisers.

headline.main: Under Deal With Google, Ads on Yahoo Could Cost 22 Percent More

abstract: In an ongoing lawsuit over copyright violations, Viacom agreed to accept information from Google on the usage of YouTube users, with identifying information replaced by anonymous code numbers. But the agreement doesn’t resolve the bigger issue that Internet users’ personal information might be released through other court actions and legal investigations.

lead_paragraph: Viacom and Google have reached an agreement about how information about YouTube users can be used as potential evidence in the ongoing copyright dispute.

headline.main: Google Will Protect Users’ Identity from Viacom — This Time
